    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Jenkins With Rails Step-by-step. Part 1]]></title>
    <link href="http://goodniceweb.me/05-11-2015/jenkins-with-rails-step-by-step.html"/>
    <updated>2015-05-11T13:38:52+03:00</updated>
    <id>http://goodniceweb.me/05-11-2015/jenkins-with-rails-step-by-step</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In <a href="http://goodniceweb.me/05-04-2015/jenkins-rails-docker-container.html">one of my recent posts</a>
you can find manual of jenkins-rails container usage. Here I want to extend it,
add some screenshots and so on.</p>

<p>At first, let&rsquo;s create new rails app.</p>

<!-- more -->




<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rails --version
</span><span class='line'>Rails 4.2.0.rc2 <span class="c"># feel free to use your version here ;)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rails new candy --skip-test-unit <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="nb">cd </span>candy
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>git init <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> git add . <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> git ci -m <span class="s2">&quot;Initial commit&quot;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Now I&rsquo;ll install <code>rspec</code> and make get some dead simple tests from scaffold.</p>

<p><a href="http://pastie.org/private/nuhg3wvcphhc0euzkd4tw">Gemfile</a></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>bundle install
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rails g rspec:install
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rails g scaffold article title content:text
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rake db:migrate
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">&#39;-f documentation&#39;</span> &gt;&gt; .rspec
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>rspec spec
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Last will must return smth. like this</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'>Finished in 0.2916 seconds
</span><span class='line'><span class="m">30</span> examples, <span class="m">0</span> failures, <span class="m">2</span> pending
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Than let&rsquo;s execute line from previous post.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='bash'><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>docker run -d <span class="se">\</span>
</span><span class='line'>    -p 8080:8080 <span class="se">\</span>
</span><span class='line'>    -v ~/your/folder:/home/jenkins_home <span class="se">\</span>
</span><span class='line'>    --name jenkins <span class="se">\</span>
</span><span class='line'>    goodniceweb/jenkins-rails:latest
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Now on visiting <a href="http://localhost:8080/">http://localhost:8080/</a> you&rsquo;ll see Jenkins dashboard screen.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/jenkins-dashboard-1.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Dashboard&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Dashboard&#34;"></p>

<p>At first here I propose to make Jenkins more secure. Click to &ldquo;Manage Jenkins&rdquo; link
and than to &ldquo;Setup Security&rdquo; button. On opened page check &ldquo;Enable security&rdquo; box.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-1.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>In &ldquo;Access Control&rdquo; section &ldquo;Security Realm&rdquo; sub-section choose &ldquo;Jenkins’ own user database&rdquo; radiobutton.
Below, in &ldquo;Authorization&rdquo; sub-section choose &ldquo;Project-based Matrix Authorization Strategy&rdquo; option.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-2.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>You&rsquo;ll able to see created table with only &lsquo;Anonymous&rsquo; user for now. We will fix it later.
At first let&rsquo;s add &lsquo;Read&rsquo; permission to Anonymous user. Just tick according checkbox.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-3.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>Ok, now the time for creating admin user. Focus this input&hellip;</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-4.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>&hellip; write &lsquo;admin&rsquo; and press &ldquo;Add&rdquo; button. Then scroll horisontally, if its need,
and press on this little icon. All checkboxes should be chosen for admin, right?</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-5.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>Perfect. Now I propose to save your changes. Press &ldquo;Save&rdquo; button underneath.
You should be redirected to login page after this because now you are Anonymous user.
Don&rsquo;t worry, directly after registration you&rsquo;ll be able to continue configuring Jenkins.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/registration.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Registration&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Registration&#34;"></p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/jenkins-dashboard-2.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Security Settings&#34;"></p>

<p>Super awesome. Now time to initialize our project. Press &ldquo;create new jobs&rdquo; on main page
or &ldquo;New Item&rdquo; link. Than choose a name and select &ldquo;Freestyle project&rdquo; option. Press &ldquo;OK&rdquo;.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/new-project.png" title="&#34;Jenkins New Rails Project&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins New Rails Project&#34;"></p>

<p>Then you&rsquo;ll see Job Settings page. Few things here need to be configured:</p>

<ol>
<li><p>Security settings. Check &ldquo;Enable project-based security&rdquo; box. Add your &lsquo;admin&rsquo; user with all permissions.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/security-6.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Security&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Security&#34;"></p></li>
<li><p>Choose &ldquo;Git&rdquo; from &ldquo;Source Code Management&rdquo; section. Install your credentials.
I prefer to use https with login/password for this test.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-1.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;">
<img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-2.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;">
<img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-3.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;"></p></li>
<li><p>Install push hooks and rvm settings.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-4.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;"></p></li>
<li><p>Insert build script for testing project</p>

<p>I prefer to use smth. like this:</p>

<pre><code class="bash">bundle install --without production --deployment
cp -f config/database.yml.example config/database.yml
cp -f config/secrets.yml.example config/secrets.yml
bundle exec rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV=test 
bundle exec rspec spec 
</code></pre>

<p>Here we make sure that we had latest gem and database settings.
Also we place secrets.yml file, update db state and run the tests.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-5.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;"></p></li>
<li><p>Let&rsquo;s create email notification for failing cases.</p>

<p><img src="http://goodniceweb.me/images/jenkins-rails-comprehensive-guide/project-settings-6.png" title="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;" alt="&#34;Jenkins Project Settings&#34;"></p></li>
</ol>


<p>That&rsquo;s it. Pressing &ldquo;Save&rdquo; button will redirect us to main Job page. There we can trigger manual build
for check is our configuration work or not.</p>

<p>I hope you can follow this steps. If something went wrong and you have no idea how to handle it, please
feel free to write below in comments. I&rsquo;ll help with pleasure :)</p>

<p>Please, see <a href="#">second part</a> for next steps.</p>
]]></content>
